  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "We convert the received block header timestamp to a int64 here: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/develop/core/block_processor.go#L356\n\nA malicious miner can set a timestamp value that will overflow a int64 into a value that is valid according to consensus rules. This breaks consensus as two different block headers (hashes) would be considered the same by the Go consensus validations.\n\nConverting to a uint type here is enough to avoid this as block times will always be positive integers in UNIX time.\n\nTODO: verify what scalar value size will be accepted here in terms of RLP - we could potentially have a overflow on any uint too.\n",
